<h2>Ready to run in Charity Challenge this Sunday</h2>
</div>
<p></p>
<p>10.12.12</p>
<div class="newsbody"><p>The final details are being put into place as our 2012 Matthew House team is getting ready to run in the Scotia bank Marathon, Half Marathon and 5 km event this Sunday October 14th.&nbsp; We have a smaller team than last year but still a great group with great spirit!&nbsp; We have the largest number of former residents ever participating from countries such as: Afghanistan, Eritrea, Somalia, Iran, Zimbabwe, Botswana and Ethiopia.&nbsp; Rain or shine, we are ready and have participants in all three distances from 5K to the marathon!&nbsp; <strong>And there is still time to put pledges on our team members</strong>!&nbsp; Our former residents would especially benefit from outsider support since they have less of a social network to call upon.&nbsp;<strong> <a href="http://run4matthewhouse.wordpress.com/">CLICK HERE</a> </strong>to read&nbsp;ALL about&nbsp;the race.&nbsp; You can also&nbsp;see our <a href="http://my.e2rm.com/TeamPage.aspx?teamID=284100&amp;langPref=en-CA&amp;Referrer=http%3a%2f%2fwww.torontowaterfrontmarathon.com%2fen%2fcharity.htm"><strong>TEAM LIST HERE</strong></a> and&nbsp; sponsor a Matthew House team member.</p>
<p>Go MH team go!!&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;And thanks for your support!!</p></div>
